For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Tiffany M. Smith in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 10:55 am.  State gives plea agreement, waive p.h. plea to charge however move to delete school enhancer, withheld sentence 2 years probation AODA follow through,  counseling, 15 days jail, costs, reserve right for expungement 973.015 if complete successfully complete probation, DNA sample & surcharge, Parties agrees to plea agreement.  Waiver of Preliminary Examination filed.  Def. waives p.h.  Court accepts waiver & finds freely & voluntarily given.  Information Filed. Atty Schuster has copy of information & waives reading.  Plea questionnaire & waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands form.  Mnf/Dlvr THC 961.41(1)(h)1, Guilty plea.   Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understands elements. Atty Schuster is satisfied. Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given, Factual basis stipulated. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to Delivery of THC 961.41(1)(H)1. State gives sentencing statement.  Atty Schuster gives sentencing statement. Def. makes statement. Court orders on Ct. 1 withheld prison sentence 2 years probation, AODA & follow through, Counseling deemed appropriate by agent, courts costs, 15 days jail, c. 1-23-16 @ 6 pm. or any time sooner, huber privileges, Benefit to def. Can be served in any other county in State of WI,  no electronic monitoring, DNA Sample & $250 surcharge. Court will find in the interest of def. or public will reserve def's rights for expungement under 973.015, after 2 years if successfully completes probation, no crimes @ level of p.c. & all court obligations paid.  Def. advised of firearm & voting rights.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Def. advised of postconviction rights.  Review hearing scheduled for November 28, 2017 at 01:00 pm.
